We are so grateful and excited to expand Vaca’s Creamery! In April 2021, we launched a Kickstarter campaign to open a vegan soft serve walkup window in Chicago and publish an original cookbook of vegan desserts. Now the book is out, we have two locations (one with fresh baked pastries every day), and are looking forward to our biggest summer ever!
Thank you to the wonderful Vaca’s staff and the people of Chicago (and the many who come from out of town) for giving us the opportunity to feed you delicious vegan desserts. Every day we work to improve our recipes, expand our offerings, and build an ice cream shop that uplifts animals instead of exploiting them. 
Thank you in advance for understanding the growing pains we will likely experience once Chicago summer stops being so coy. We may run out of items on occasion and soft serve ice cream machines aren’t famous for being unbreakable, but we plan to eventually expand our hours and offerings at both locations. We also have a few surprises planned for 2023, so keep an eye out!

We love you!

Story time 📖
Once upon a time a person in our production team (who shall remain nameless) decided they were too good to be dependent on coffee. They were no longer going to be bound by the shackles of caffeine. The plan was going well until, faced with the task of making chocolate-covered potato chips + peanut butter pints, they added in brownies. Yes, it’s a good combination, and we can understand why one’s brain may lead there. Not different enough from our choc-potato-pb pint though. Fortunately, we had a great idea. We added sprinkles and M&Not’s, and called it Piñata! The day (and the batch of ice cream) was saved. The moral of the story is: we have very few of these pints (at Lincoln Square), we will not be making them again, and drink coffee (which we have too).
